text:
There once was a man called Guitarro. 
He said, See the great scolaro! 
From nach spiel's side, 
He guitarred wide, 
He couldn't resist the finocchiaro.

There once was a man from ocean. 
He said, See the great hand lotion! 
It was rather southern, 
But not very cothern, 
And he couldn't resist the laotian.

There once was an elephant from savanna. 
He said, See the lovely cana! 
It was quite tropical, 
But not semitropical, 
And he couldn't resist the atlanta.

There once was a old man from war. 
He said, See the great troubadour! 
It was rather long, 
But not very klong,
He just couldn't say no to the for.

Beyond the nach spiel 
A stringed, little guitar plays 
at the perfect notes

Cheery summertime 
before scuba diving dives 
on the ocean floor

Loving summertime 
A young, elephant snorking 
watching the savanna

Meandering thoughts 
 An underground, big tanks shoots 
whilst watching the dead

Guitar 
Guitar playing, show-off 
Jerk, string, note 
Ever so acoustic 
Lost

Scuba diving 
Diving suited, wet 
Diving, swimming, exlporing 
Sometimes I'd dream about jet ski 
Found

Elephant 
Huge, gray 
Snorking, eating, playing trumpet 
It made me feel big 
Mammoth

War 
Bloody, loud 
Tanks, weapon, sergeant 
Making the world civil 
Gone
